02:20.377 --> 02:22.655
What dirty Beelzebub are you?

02:22.679 --> 02:27.093
You horny, stinking,
Lord of Flies fed on

02:27.117 --> 02:30.129
dung and garbage stew!

02:31.855 --> 02:34.133
We won't attend your revelries!

02:34.157 --> 02:36.675
You putrid, Slonikan fish!

02:37.928 --> 02:40.713
And festered eye
compose your flesh...

02:42.432 --> 02:46.352
Or is it, as
your friends report,

02:47.204 --> 02:50.989
your mother let a liquid fart.

02:55.378 --> 02:57.930
Death to illusions!

04:13.556 --> 04:16.742
You are coming
with us, Mr. Jacob.

04:25.035 --> 04:27.446
Then, set your hand free,

04:27.470 --> 04:31.056
and let your instincts

04:31.084 --> 04:35.770
carry your pencil
to its destination.

04:51.571 --> 04:53.148
Where are you going?

04:53.172 --> 04:54.583
I have plans.

04:54.607 --> 04:56.085
Well, change them.

04:56.109 --> 04:57.653
I have already
seen you three days this week.

04:57.677 --> 05:01.223
You told me we shouldn't
spend too much time together.

05:01.247 --> 05:02.825
I'm just trying to
follow your rules.

05:02.849 --> 05:06.595
Rules? I despise rules.

05:06.619 --> 05:09.565
Do as you please.

05:09.589 --> 05:12.574
I'll take Dora to lunch.
You don't mind, do you?

05:16.395 --> 05:18.947
Have a lovely time.

05:21.601 --> 05:23.451
She is a child, Pablo.

05:24.036 --> 05:26.215
You'll only spoil
her for someone else.

05:26.239 --> 05:28.584
You're more
narrow-minded than a bishop.

05:30.276 --> 05:32.346
She's totally capable of
looking out for herself.

05:32.645 --> 05:34.089
Monsieur Cocteau.

05:34.113 --> 05:35.591
I'm sorry to barge in.

05:35.615 --> 05:37.699
John!

05:38.151 --> 05:40.729
I've received a letter from Max.

05:40.753 --> 05:43.038
He's been arrested
by the Gestapo.

05:44.423 --> 05:45.901
They hauled him off to Drancy,

05:45.925 --> 05:49.210
but that's just a temporary
stop before they ship him east.

05:49.729 --> 05:52.213
Poor Max. You know,
I-I tried to warn him.

05:52.632 --> 05:56.384
I've drafted a petition to the
German embassy asking for his release.

05:56.669 --> 05:59.020
Everyone signed it...

06:08.514 --> 06:10.632
I can't.

06:11.350 --> 06:14.936
For God's sake, Pablo,
th-the man is sick as it is.

06:15.021 --> 06:18.006
He won't survive in a camp.

06:18.724 --> 06:21.176
The Nazis hate me, John.

06:22.829 --> 06:25.347
They have threatened to
throw me into a camp.

06:27.466 --> 06:30.552
They outlawed my art and
denounce me in speeches and,

06:32.572 --> 06:36.191
my signature would
do Max more harm than help.

06:36.909 --> 06:39.388
Send the letter without my name.

06:39.412 --> 06:41.796
Before it's too late.

06:52.291 --> 06:54.642
Where have you been?

06:55.761 --> 06:58.747
Chasing after
your new plaything?

06:59.498 --> 07:01.510
I've had a terrible day.

07:01.534 --> 07:04.886
I had my bicycle snatched right out
of my hands on the Rue d'Athenes.

07:09.575 --> 07:12.360
You see that man?

07:12.812 --> 07:15.897
He's been staring at
me since I sat down.

07:16.515 --> 07:19.434
I think he's following me.

07:22.154 --> 07:26.041
Did I tell you how Rene Drouin has
asked me to do a show at his gallery?

07:27.193 --> 07:29.304
He wants to change
the dates again.

07:29.328 --> 07:33.615
How am I supposed to prepare
if he can't make up his mind?

07:38.371 --> 07:40.949
Have you heard a word I've said?

07:40.973 --> 07:43.485
You are not the
only one with problems, Dora.

07:43.509 --> 07:46.294
Something terrible
has happened to Max.

07:50.082 --> 07:52.628
Max. What a surprise.

07:52.652 --> 07:54.596
I, uh, I hope you don't mind.

07:54.620 --> 07:56.865
I heard you were back
in town, and, and, uh...

07:56.889 --> 07:59.707
I, I, I'm glad to see you.

07:59.859 --> 08:02.504
What, uh, what
happened between us, uh...

08:02.528 --> 08:04.573
It was a, a hard
time for all of us.

08:04.597 --> 08:10.452
I care for you, of course,
but I am, I am not, um, yeah.

08:11.170 --> 08:14.589
Max. It's all right.

08:15.675 --> 08:18.086
I have, uh, met someone.

08:18.110 --> 08:20.188
How wonderful. Um.

08:20.212 --> 08:21.590
Yep. Yeah.

08:21.614 --> 08:23.091
Who is he?

08:23.115 --> 08:25.093
No. No, no, no. No, no.

08:25.117 --> 08:26.595
A woman. Yeah.

08:26.619 --> 08:28.096
Oh.

08:28.120 --> 08:31.033
Her name is Cecile.
She is, uh...

08:31.057 --> 08:34.642
Something, really. She's...

08:42.702 --> 08:49.269
Oh. I see that you have
your eye on someone, too.

08:49.270 --> 08:53.027
Oh. No,
she's-she's just a neighbor.

08:53.479 --> 08:56.792
Just a neighbor.
And what is her name?

08:56.816 --> 09:00.335
I don't even know.

09:01.087 --> 09:03.098
Invite me in.

09:03.122 --> 09:08.307
I want to see what, uh, you've been up
to and most importantly, I need a drink.

09:08.308 --> 09:11.473
Actually, I was
just on my way out.

09:11.497 --> 09:13.815
Why don't you come with me?

09:15.468 --> 09:16.778
700.

09:16.802 --> 09:18.313
Each?

09:18.337 --> 09:19.614
For all three.

09:19.638 --> 09:21.049
Piss off, Sagot.

09:21.073 --> 09:22.818
I wouldn't let them
go for twice that.

09:22.842 --> 09:25.587
If you don't like it,
try your luck with Soulie.

09:25.611 --> 09:27.823
But don't forget you
still owe me the money

09:27.847 --> 09:29.855
that I advanced you
for the pigment.

09:31.183 --> 09:33.401
Let's go, Max.

09:33.452 --> 09:36.771
I know a place where people
actually appreciate modern art.

09:41.460 --> 09:44.212
Henri Matisse?

09:44.764 --> 09:47.649
The drawing is rudimentary.
Worse than a child's.

09:48.200 --> 09:50.012
And the perspective is flat.

09:50.036 --> 09:52.720
Clouds are
yellow, skin is purple.

09:53.139 --> 09:57.692
Yes, it's-it's all wrong.
But it's magnificent.

09:58.844 --> 10:00.489
Makes no sense.

10:00.513 --> 10:02.824
Yet it's completely alive.

10:02.848 --> 10:05.293
You are twice as
talented an artist.

10:05.317 --> 10:07.162
No, this artist
has more than just talent.

10:07.186 --> 10:10.104
He has vision.

10:10.723 --> 10:13.635
I have never painted
anything this revolutionary.

10:13.659 --> 10:15.804
But you could.

10:15.828 --> 10:19.414
Yes. But I need to find
a new way of seeing things.

10:19.565 --> 10:22.144
Like this man has.
He understands.

10:22.168 --> 10:24.146
Understands what?

10:24.170 --> 10:26.882
That we don't need artists to
show us what people look like anymore.

10:26.906 --> 10:29.051
We have photographs for that.

10:29.075 --> 10:32.387
This Matisse is showing
us a deeper truth.

10:32.411 --> 10:34.322
The way things
are in our dreams.

10:34.346 --> 10:36.898
Not just as they appear to be.

10:38.017 --> 10:45.212
He has bent all the rules,
and I want to smash them.

10:48.661 --> 10:51.279
I have someone you should meet.

10:58.204 --> 11:02.390
Apollinaire. That can't
actually be your name.

11:02.908 --> 11:07.022
Judges and tax
assessors call me Kostrowitzky,

11:07.046 --> 11:10.869
but Apollinairus is
indeed my middle name,

11:10.893 --> 11:14.602
inscribed on my birth
records in Rome and

11:14.603 --> 11:20.908
ordained by destiny in honor of Apollo,
the deity of the Delphic Oracle.

11:22.795 --> 11:26.481
You're even more
full of yourself than I am.

11:35.741 --> 11:39.627
I think I
like your Spanish friend.

11:41.447 --> 11:44.899
Absinthe! The green muse.

11:55.661 --> 11:58.907
As artistes, we must
demand nothing less than the

11:58.931 --> 12:02.784
perpetual immoral subversion
of the existing order.

12:06.005 --> 12:07.549
Oh...

12:07.573 --> 12:13.027
Look out! Hey!
You'll get yourself killed.

12:15.247 --> 12:18.522
And if he did die, do you

12:18.546 --> 12:22.221
know what he might see
on the other side?

12:22.855 --> 12:26.007
Tell me.

12:26.325 --> 12:29.444
I will show you instead.

12:40.506 --> 12:41.883
Clowns?

12:41.907 --> 12:45.259
Not just clowns, Harlequins.

12:47.246 --> 12:50.158
What is the difference?

12:50.182 --> 12:54.602
Look closely.
There is evil behind those eyes.

12:58.157 --> 13:01.242
Everyone thinks that
Harlequins are entertainers,

13:03.295 --> 13:06.007
but that is
merely their disguise.

13:06.031 --> 13:12.834
They are actually,
devils, escaped from hell.

13:22.514 --> 13:26.296
Your picture is,
um, too symbolist.

13:26.552 --> 13:27.696
Oh, really?

13:27.720 --> 13:28.863
Mm.

13:28.887 --> 13:32.607
And what have
you written tonight?

13:34.026 --> 13:39.154
My poem is, um,
oh, oh, oh! Right here.

13:39.732 --> 13:43.511
It is just waiting for me
to pour it upon the page.

13:43.535 --> 13:47.221
It is, uh, much too cheerful.

13:48.173 --> 13:49.484
The acrobat, you mean?

13:49.508 --> 13:51.319
Yeah, he is so pretty.

13:51.343 --> 13:55.296
You might as well
be an Impressionist.

13:55.347 --> 13:58.526
Perpetual immoral subversion.

13:58.550 --> 14:00.662
It's not pretty pictures.

14:00.686 --> 14:02.651
If you want to outdo
Matisse, you must use

14:02.675 --> 14:04.696
your images the way
that I use my words.

14:05.257 --> 14:07.068
You must shatter
all the conventions.

14:07.092 --> 14:09.771
You must stun them
with perversity.

14:09.795 --> 14:14.749
He is right.
Sweet little dancing nymphs!

14:16.635 --> 14:20.382
They will not rattle any
bones at the Autumn Salon.

14:20.406 --> 14:23.551
Why didn't you
say something before?

14:23.575 --> 14:26.987
You draw so damn quickly,
I didn't realize it until just now.

14:26.988 --> 14:29.591
His trouble is, he's too sober.

14:29.615 --> 14:32.794
That's always a problem
of course, but right now, uh,

14:32.818 --> 14:34.929
my trouble is I will
miss the last train.

14:34.953 --> 14:36.685
No, you can't leave. I need more

14:36.709 --> 14:38.600
pretentious poetry and
heartless criticism.

14:38.624 --> 14:40.268
If I'm going to fix
this damn painting.

14:40.292 --> 14:41.936
I can't stay
all night, every night.

14:41.960 --> 14:44.812
I've got other, uh, commitments.

14:45.097 --> 14:47.482
What commitments?

15:00.512 --> 15:01.990
Where have you been?

15:02.014 --> 15:03.958
Drinking English ale
with the riff raff again.

15:03.982 --> 15:06.294
Please, mother. It's late.

15:06.318 --> 15:09.164
Do you expect me to support
you until you are 40 years old?

15:09.188 --> 15:10.465
What more do you want from me?

15:10.489 --> 15:12.233
I bring home a pay
check every month!

15:12.257 --> 15:15.917
Yes! And you waste
it all in bars and cabarets.

15:16.161 --> 15:19.075
And now Monsieur Maurice has complained
about your work at the bank.

15:19.076 --> 15:21.676
I don't care about Monsieur
Maurice and his godforsaken bank.

15:21.700 --> 15:23.511
I am a poet, not a peon.

15:23.535 --> 15:27.349
The only place you are a
poet is in your gin-addled brain.

15:27.373 --> 15:30.285
Do you know what I had to
do to get you that job?

15:30.309 --> 15:34.926
If you lose it, I won't think twice
about throwing you out on the street.

16:05.978 --> 16:09.597
Well, you are a sorry
little bugger, aren't you?

16:20.325 --> 16:23.611
It looks like you're not the only
one who got caught in the rain.

16:24.997 --> 16:28.243
The poor thing. Is it yours?

16:28.267 --> 16:32.320
Well... I suppose she is now.

16:32.871 --> 16:34.849
What should I call her?

16:34.873 --> 16:37.752
My aunt had a cat named Minou.

16:37.776 --> 16:43.150
Perfect.
And what should I call you?

16:44.450 --> 16:46.934
Fernande.

16:47.453 --> 16:49.931
Why don't you come
to my studio, Fernande?

16:49.955 --> 16:53.871
Give the kitten some-some
milk and you some hot tea.

16:53.959 --> 16:57.979
I can't, I'm, I'm expected.

17:01.366 --> 17:04.618
Poor Minou,
she's, very disappointed.

17:11.643 --> 17:13.887
Don't you ever clean?

17:13.912 --> 17:17.067
If I disturb the dust,
it gets on the paintings.

17:17.549 --> 17:19.560
Destroys them.

17:19.585 --> 17:22.230
Your paintings
must be very precious to you.

17:22.253 --> 17:26.272
They're everything.
Ah. Hold the kitty tight.

17:27.659 --> 17:28.870
Why?

17:28.894 --> 17:32.213
I want to show you my lodger.

17:37.769 --> 17:40.354
You are very kind to strays.

17:45.844 --> 17:47.455
You paint clowns?

17:47.479 --> 17:49.257
Harlequins.

17:49.281 --> 17:52.126
Most of the artists I
know prefer to paint naked women.

17:52.150 --> 17:55.002
I prefer not to paint
what everyone else does.

17:55.254 --> 17:57.599
I'm submitting it
to the Autumn Salon.

17:57.623 --> 17:59.901
I went last year.

17:59.925 --> 18:04.645
This looks, well, not like
any of the paintings I saw.

18:05.664 --> 18:07.442
That's exactly the point.

18:07.466 --> 18:10.718
I want to shake the judges out of
their frock coats and cravats.

18:10.836 --> 18:12.180
It's a new century.

18:12.204 --> 18:13.982
Everything is changing.

18:14.006 --> 18:16.824
Art must change, too.

18:18.544 --> 18:22.096
Most painters just want
someone to buy their pictures.

18:23.148 --> 18:26.801
That's being a
whore, not an artist.

18:27.486 --> 18:30.938
There's no
shame in making a living.

18:34.960 --> 18:37.939
I've been meaning to
talk to you for a long time,

18:37.963 --> 18:41.182
but you're
always in such a hurry.

18:43.201 --> 18:46.353
Who are they?

18:46.638 --> 18:50.291
Some people I
saw at the Lapin Agile.

18:51.376 --> 18:55.229
She looks like she
wants to get away from him.

18:59.251 --> 19:02.703
What's wrong?

19:04.189 --> 19:07.575
It's as though you've
already drawn my picture.

19:09.528 --> 19:16.858
No. I don't know if I could
ever draw someone as beautiful as you.

19:52.471 --> 19:54.082
What are you doing?

19:54.106 --> 19:55.617
Drawing.

19:55.641 --> 19:57.218
I didn't say you could do that.

19:57.242 --> 19:58.786
Sorry. I thought...

19:58.810 --> 20:00.455
People pay me to model for them.

20:00.479 --> 20:02.863
I don't do it for free.

20:03.849 --> 20:04.926
Where are you going?

20:04.950 --> 20:06.361
This was a mistake.

20:06.385 --> 20:08.229
Laurent will ask
1,000 questions.

20:08.253 --> 20:10.398
Where have I been?
Who was I with?

20:10.422 --> 20:13.007
This can never happen again.

20:23.451 --> 20:27.039
The Gestapo don't know the
first thing about poetry.

20:27.063 --> 20:30.107
I am quite certain they
have no appreciation

20:30.131 --> 20:32.645
for the talents of
your little Jew.

20:32.669 --> 20:35.654
Um, he is a Catholic, actually.

20:35.839 --> 20:38.657
I wouldn't repeat that
fiction to anyone else.

20:38.675 --> 20:40.286
No, of course, Minister.

20:40.310 --> 20:43.089
Now, that's not
his only difficulty.

20:43.113 --> 20:48.346
It's well known that he has
certain deviant predilections.

20:52.255 --> 20:59.344
He-He's revered in France
as, uh, an idol to our youth and...

20:59.429 --> 21:03.749
He invented an entirely
new language of poetry.

21:04.134 --> 21:07.920
Personally, I'm rather
partial to the symbolists.

21:08.038 --> 21:14.796
But, despite his pretentions, I agree
Jacob's words have a certain power.

21:16.012 --> 21:17.356
You've read him?

21:17.380 --> 21:20.399
We are not all
philistines, Monsieur Cocteau.

21:20.517 --> 21:25.070
Then, you understand how
much he means to-to the French.

21:25.288 --> 21:29.975
Indeed, and you do have some
rather influential friends in Vichy.

21:32.362 --> 21:35.113
I'll see what we can do.

21:40.603 --> 21:41.586
May I help you?

21:41.610 --> 21:44.705
I have release papers
for prisoner 15872.

21:46.643 --> 21:49.261
- Jacob?
- Yes.

21:50.013 --> 21:55.115
I'm sorry. Monsieur
Jacob died last night.

21:58.121 --> 22:00.873
What...

22:06.329 --> 22:09.314
The service is starting.

22:11.701 --> 22:14.003
I should have
dragged him out of that

22:14.027 --> 22:16.330
monastery and put him
on a boat to America!

22:16.873 --> 22:20.019
You are not the king, Pablo.

22:20.043 --> 22:23.989
You could not force Max to do
something he didn't want to do.

22:24.013 --> 22:26.592
He died alone.

22:26.616 --> 22:32.104
In a cold room on a dirty cot.
This damn war is almost over.

22:32.322 --> 22:36.193
If only he could have stayed
hidden for a few more months.

22:41.197 --> 22:46.585
He had a good life. He had God.

22:50.607 --> 22:53.052
Now come inside and
say goodbye to him.

22:53.076 --> 22:57.790
No, no, I-I said goodbye
to him last year in Loiret. No.

22:57.814 --> 23:00.559
If you don't pay your last
respects, you'll regret it.

23:00.583 --> 23:03.129
No, I want to remember
him alive, not dead in a coffin.

23:03.153 --> 23:06.371
I'll only see
myself lying there. No.

23:07.657 --> 23:10.469
I wouldn't worry
about dying, Pablo.

23:10.493 --> 23:13.879
I'm sure you are
immortal like a vampire.

23:15.632 --> 23:17.710
What is wrong with you?

23:17.734 --> 23:24.083
Have you been drinking?
I'm going home.

23:24.107 --> 23:25.551
Why?

23:25.575 --> 23:27.653
So you can climb into bed
with your little girlfriend?

23:27.677 --> 23:29.221
To feel young again?

23:29.245 --> 23:32.164
What a marvelous idea.

23:46.329 --> 23:49.141
Hey, toots, I was here first.
Wait your turn.

23:49.165 --> 23:50.776
How about a date, mademoiselle?

23:50.800 --> 23:52.985
I got chocolate.

23:53.703 --> 23:56.015
Who are all these people, Jaime?

23:56.039 --> 23:58.154
They put his
face on the cover of a

23:58.178 --> 24:00.186
magazine, now everyone
wants his autograph.

24:00.210 --> 24:02.121
So, why are you here?

24:02.145 --> 24:05.024
Oh, well, Pablo invited
me to the Catalan to celebrate.

24:05.048 --> 24:06.759
He's not here.

24:06.783 --> 24:10.535
He's with Dora, they're choosing
work for her gallery show.

