Mademoiselle, you seem like
an intelligent young woman,

24:14.491 --> 24:18.170
you must know the
kind of man he is.

24:18.194 --> 24:20.806
What do you mean?

24:20.830 --> 24:22.808
He is a genius.

24:22.832 --> 24:24.808
He thinks it gives
him the right to

24:24.832 --> 24:27.285
demand of everyone,
especially his women,

24:27.504 --> 24:30.789
to cater to his whims.

24:31.140 --> 24:34.620
He's been like
this for 50 years.

24:34.644 --> 24:38.196
Do you really think he's
going to change for you?

24:40.316 --> 24:42.361
Should I come back tomorrow?

24:42.385 --> 24:45.303
Why not stay a bit longer?

24:45.355 --> 24:46.832
We agreed on three hours.

24:46.856 --> 24:51.076
Yes, for five francs,
but, I have 10.

24:53.563 --> 24:54.974
My neck hurts.

24:54.998 --> 24:56.675
I don't think I can
pose any more today.

24:56.699 --> 25:00.385
And I can't paint anymore, so
why don't you get comfortable?

25:01.538 --> 25:05.257
I will rub your neck.

25:07.443 --> 25:10.595
Pig.

25:13.583 --> 25:15.060
So, how much did he give you?

25:15.084 --> 25:16.328
I earned it.

25:16.352 --> 25:19.404
I don't need to report
every centime to you.

25:19.422 --> 25:21.200
So you expect me
to pay for everything, huh?

25:21.224 --> 25:24.676
The food? The rent?

25:24.727 --> 25:26.939
Maybe if you made a sculpture
someone actually wanted to buy,

25:26.963 --> 25:29.575
you wouldn't have to
take all my money.

25:29.599 --> 25:30.976
You ungrateful bitch!

25:31.000 --> 25:34.013
Fernande. Are you all right?

25:34.037 --> 25:36.048
Mind your business,
Spaniard, or I'll report you to

25:36.072 --> 25:39.257
the immigration authorities.

25:39.275 --> 25:41.865
You don't have to let him
treat you this way, Fernande.

25:41.978 --> 25:45.730
Knock on my door anytime,
and I'll help you.

25:47.984 --> 25:50.629
Why is he
talking to you like that?

25:50.653 --> 25:53.705
Hmm? Who is he to you?

25:53.790 --> 25:56.735
No one. Look at his eyes.

25:56.759 --> 25:59.644
He's a lunatic. Leave us alone.

26:14.010 --> 26:15.788
"Everything enchants Picasso.

26:15.812 --> 26:17.556
The delightful and the horrible.

26:17.580 --> 26:19.592
The abject and the delicate.

26:19.616 --> 26:22.127
His new masterpiece,
'Saltimbanques' strikes like

26:22.151 --> 26:24.970
a sword in the heart of
those who cling to history."

26:25.021 --> 26:31.831
Oh, it is powerful, Guillaume, but,
uh, since when are you an art critic?

26:31.832 --> 26:35.507
Since I discovered La
Plume pays 20 francs per review.

26:35.531 --> 26:37.009
What?

26:37.033 --> 26:39.311
I submitted
it for the next issue.

26:39.335 --> 26:42.296
Why don't you let me finish
the bloody painting before you try

26:42.297 --> 26:44.689
and publish articles about it?

26:52.348 --> 26:54.866
Watch where you're going.

26:55.151 --> 26:58.069
You are the one who's in
the way, you little Dago.

27:04.794 --> 27:07.712
Come on, let's go.

27:07.997 --> 27:09.208
Let go of me!

27:09.232 --> 27:10.776
What the hell were you thinking?

27:10.800 --> 27:12.044
The man is twice your size.

27:12.068 --> 27:13.345
You could have gotten
yourself killed.

27:13.369 --> 27:14.713
The bastard deserved it.

27:14.737 --> 27:18.350
What is wrong?
I've never seen you like this.

27:18.374 --> 27:21.220
Just, exhausted, I suppose.

27:21.244 --> 27:25.829
Well, maybe you should, uh, try
sleeping instead of painting all night.

27:25.830 --> 27:28.060
How am I supposed to paint,
when I have to listen to the

27:28.084 --> 27:29.962
girl next door getting
screwed all night long?

27:29.986 --> 27:31.130
What girl?

27:31.154 --> 27:33.132
Fernande.

27:33.156 --> 27:36.793
Oh, I thought you
did not know her name.

27:37.193 --> 27:38.871
What, the one
who lives with the sculptor?

27:38.895 --> 27:41.073
I can't understand what
the hell she's doing with him!

27:41.097 --> 27:42.408
Oh, for Christ's sake.

27:42.432 --> 27:43.976
You're in love with her.

27:44.000 --> 27:45.377
Of course I'm not.

27:45.401 --> 27:46.979
You can't sleep, you can't work.

27:47.003 --> 27:48.547
You are jealous of
the man she's with.

27:48.571 --> 27:50.749
Ah, he's right.

27:50.773 --> 27:53.387
You just do not recognize
the signs because,

27:53.411 --> 27:55.941
uh, it has never
happened to you before.

27:57.947 --> 28:00.693
Well, if-if this is what
love feels like, I-I don't want it.

28:00.717 --> 28:04.302
Good. Because love
destroys and you must create.

28:04.554 --> 28:06.732
The Autumn Salon is less
than two weeks away.

28:06.756 --> 28:10.108
This is your chance to spit in the face
of the masters, to shake the world,

28:10.326 --> 28:13.845
to stun Matisse.

28:14.263 --> 28:16.375
You've worked so hard
on Saltimbanques.

28:16.399 --> 28:17.840
Are you really going
to throw it away over

28:17.864 --> 28:19.178
some fantasy about
another man's lover?

28:19.202 --> 28:20.412
She does not love him.

28:20.436 --> 28:22.681
For Christ's sake!

28:22.705 --> 28:25.584
Would you forget this tart?

28:25.608 --> 28:29.694
Just go home and
finish your painting.

29:04.925 --> 29:06.937
I need to talk to you.

29:06.961 --> 29:08.672
Did you follow me down here?

29:08.696 --> 29:11.108
I just wanted a
moment alone with you.

29:11.132 --> 29:12.809
What happened
was a mistake, Pablo.

29:12.833 --> 29:14.344
I told you not to
bother me anymore.

29:14.368 --> 29:16.680
It wasn't a mistake.
It was beautiful.

29:16.704 --> 29:19.355
I know you felt the same.

29:19.406 --> 29:21.384
I love you, Fernande.

29:21.408 --> 29:23.620
I loved you the very
first moment I saw you.

29:23.644 --> 29:25.555
You're making
a fool of yourself.

29:25.579 --> 29:27.491
Well, maybe I am.

29:27.515 --> 29:30.127
But that pig you're living with has no
right to treat you the way he does.

29:30.151 --> 29:32.062
What do you want from me?

29:32.086 --> 29:33.864
Move into my studio.

29:33.888 --> 29:35.665
I'll protect you from Laurent.

29:35.689 --> 29:38.468
I'll take care of you.
I'll be good to you.

29:38.492 --> 29:40.704
Do you know how many men
have said things like that to me?

29:40.728 --> 29:41.972
I'm not like other men.

29:41.996 --> 29:44.141
All of them.
But you're all liars.

29:44.165 --> 29:47.717
No, no. I swear
on my mother's virtue.

29:48.035 --> 29:49.379
Why should I trust you?

29:49.403 --> 29:51.348
Fernande.

29:51.372 --> 29:54.482
And why in God's name would
I trade one broke artist for another?

29:57.077 --> 29:58.421
I'll take your offer.

29:58.445 --> 30:00.757
What offer?

30:00.781 --> 30:02.526
The 700 francs.

30:02.550 --> 30:04.027
Ah.

30:04.051 --> 30:07.470
I'm told 700 is what Vollard
has paid for a new Matisse.

30:07.822 --> 30:09.933
A masterpiece.

30:09.957 --> 30:11.902
I'm offering
you three paintings.

30:11.926 --> 30:13.943
Ooh.

30:15.429 --> 30:17.847
I will offer you
500 for all of them.

30:18.199 --> 30:21.684
Less, of course, the money
you owe me for the pigment.

30:22.136 --> 30:25.121
To hell with you, Sagot.

30:37.151 --> 30:38.595
I'll take the 500.

30:38.619 --> 30:40.797
Ah, that was two minutes ago.

30:40.821 --> 30:45.775
The offer now is 300.

30:47.661 --> 30:50.780
He's a goddamn thief.
300 francs.

30:51.265 --> 30:54.350
What the hell am I supposed
to do with a lousy 300 francs?

30:54.602 --> 30:57.946
Two years ago you would've
thought that a fortune.

30:58.172 --> 30:59.950
We could feast for a month.

30:59.974 --> 31:01.718
Don't you see?

31:01.742 --> 31:05.288
I wanted to show Fernande that I'm
not just another poor artist.

31:05.312 --> 31:07.005
To get her out of
Bateau-Lavoir, take-take

31:07.029 --> 31:08.391
a fancy apartment
in Montparnasse.

31:08.415 --> 31:09.700
And then what? You'd be

31:09.724 --> 31:11.261
blissfully content and
start painting again?

31:11.285 --> 31:13.536
Yes.

31:15.356 --> 31:18.523
Well, if winning this girl

31:18.547 --> 31:22.020
is the only way to get
you working again,

31:22.696 --> 31:25.141
we'll just have
to make it happen. Won't we?

31:25.165 --> 31:27.010
How?

31:27.034 --> 31:29.312
There's something you
could buy plenty of for 300 francs.

31:29.336 --> 31:32.021
What?

31:37.211 --> 31:40.229
Black magic.

32:11.545 --> 32:14.030
Did you get it?

32:17.518 --> 32:20.736
Opium. The dark mistress.

32:38.739 --> 32:41.891
I'm surprised to see you.

32:44.044 --> 32:45.555
You invited me.

32:45.579 --> 32:49.298
But I wasn't sure
you'd be brave enough to come.

32:49.883 --> 32:52.829
I was curious about the art.

32:52.853 --> 32:55.638
The art? Or the artist?

33:01.428 --> 33:04.113
So how does she rate?

33:05.766 --> 33:09.519
I think she's brilliant.

33:09.837 --> 33:12.855
Tell her yourself.
I'll introduce you.

33:12.940 --> 33:14.918
No, uh, really.

33:14.942 --> 33:17.727
I just, I just wanted
to see the paintings.

33:19.646 --> 33:22.665
Perhaps another time.

33:30.057 --> 33:34.210
Why did you bother to come
if you didn't want to meet her?

33:37.331 --> 33:40.410
I suppose I was trying to
play along with your Bohemian rules.

33:40.434 --> 33:42.579
I told you, I don't have rules.

33:42.603 --> 33:45.849
Well, whatever
you call this game.

33:45.873 --> 33:48.418
It's not as easy as I
thought it would be.

33:48.442 --> 33:51.994
It's not a game. It's life.

33:53.013 --> 33:57.533
Artists must be free.
No restrictions of any kind.

33:58.018 --> 34:01.871
Dora is a Surrealist.
She-She understands.

34:02.990 --> 34:05.541
I'm not Dora.

34:05.592 --> 34:08.978
Maybe this was the-the wrong
place for the two of you to meet.

34:09.530 --> 34:12.547
Maybe we should try again in
a more comfortable setting.

34:19.440 --> 34:23.092
He invited me to
have dinner with him and Dora.

34:23.610 --> 34:26.121
He's got no
shame at all, does he?

34:26.146 --> 34:28.291
He doesn't give a
damn what anyone else thinks.

34:28.315 --> 34:32.001
In fact, the more he offends people,
the more he seems to like it.

34:32.119 --> 34:36.108
It's scandalous, but
it will certainly be interesting.

34:37.623 --> 34:39.344
It's one thing to look the other

34:39.368 --> 34:40.837
way while he sleeps
with other women,

34:40.860 --> 34:45.636
but, I won't be paraded in
public as part of his harem.

34:48.368 --> 34:52.455
You're not actually
in love with him, are you?

35:03.684 --> 35:06.062
Maybe you can have
some fun with it.

35:06.086 --> 35:09.205
Give him a taste of
his own medicine.

35:15.262 --> 35:16.339
Bonsoir.

35:16.363 --> 35:17.707
Bonsoir.

35:17.731 --> 35:19.676
I would like
you to meet Andre Beaudin.

35:19.700 --> 35:22.952
It is an honor to meet you, sir.

35:29.776 --> 35:32.561
You are a
little devil, aren't you?

35:32.679 --> 35:35.731
Well, it seems we
need another setting. Waiter.

35:36.049 --> 35:37.393
Francoise, sit next to me.

35:37.417 --> 35:39.669
I have so many
questions to ask you.

35:48.695 --> 35:51.241
I have seen your paintings.

35:51.265 --> 35:54.183
I think they're extraordinary.

35:54.268 --> 35:58.414
Well, it's true what
you say about this one, Pablo.

35:58.438 --> 36:01.190
She has excellent taste.

36:03.810 --> 36:06.529
He is very handsome.

36:11.785 --> 36:18.040
Waiter, we'll have, um,
caviar, oysters, champagne.

36:18.659 --> 36:21.277
Right away, Madame.

36:22.796 --> 36:25.614
Isn't this fun?

36:27.267 --> 36:29.819
Yeah.

36:30.404 --> 36:32.655
Another, please.

36:33.740 --> 36:36.292
Garçon. Just,
uh, bring the check please.

36:36.610 --> 36:37.987
Right away, sir...

36:38.011 --> 36:39.923
Did I tell you what
happened to me last night?

36:39.947 --> 36:41.157
No.

36:41.181 --> 36:43.293
I was walking
across the Pont Neuf.

36:43.317 --> 36:46.402
A man ran out and
snatched my little dog.

36:46.954 --> 36:49.232
Sorry, that's,
that's, that's terrible.

36:49.256 --> 36:53.754
Poor Pepe. I can't imagine what
that evil man has done with him.

36:55.762 --> 36:58.681
First, your bike's stolen.

36:59.700 --> 37:01.611
Then your dog.

37:01.635 --> 37:04.180
How many times are you
gonna tell these stories?

37:04.204 --> 37:06.749
I don't understand
why you're not more upset.

37:06.773 --> 37:08.818
You love that dog.

37:08.842 --> 37:10.684
But I am sure Francoise would

37:10.708 --> 37:12.886
rather discuss something
more interesting.

37:18.552 --> 37:22.171
It's such a clear night.
Why don't you walk me home?

37:22.456 --> 37:25.274
I am too tired for walking. Huh.

37:26.026 --> 37:27.737
That's what
happens when you get old.

37:27.761 --> 37:30.613
You quit before the
fun even begins.

37:31.064 --> 37:33.883
Go home, Dora. Go home.

37:36.536 --> 37:38.982
I suppose I'll
see you some other time.

37:39.006 --> 37:40.450
Yeah.

37:40.474 --> 37:44.160
If I'm not murdered by
hooligans on the way home.

37:46.013 --> 37:50.266
Thank you for an
interesting evening. Good night.

37:56.857 --> 38:00.276
I really should go with him.

38:01.828 --> 38:05.308
Look, I am not
a fool, Francoise. All right?

38:05.332 --> 38:09.212
It's obvious why you
brought me here tonight.

38:09.236 --> 38:12.721
It's not because you've
got an interest in me.

38:18.278 --> 38:21.464
Are you coming?

38:39.566 --> 38:41.377
Are you sure she's all right?

38:41.401 --> 38:44.180
Don't worry about Dora.

38:44.204 --> 38:47.456
Dora will be fine.

39:44.552 --> 39:46.596
I told you to leave me alone.

39:46.620 --> 39:49.024
What if I told
you I have something

39:49.048 --> 39:51.265
that can take away
all your sadness?

39:59.533 --> 40:01.912
You cleaned.

40:01.936 --> 40:04.381
I did it for you.

40:04.405 --> 40:07.257
You didn't seem
to like it dirty.

40:08.242 --> 40:11.027
What about the dust?
Your paintings?

40:11.545 --> 40:14.597
I just want
you to be comfortable.

40:19.954 --> 40:22.132
Do you know what this is?

40:22.156 --> 40:23.633
For opium.

40:23.657 --> 40:25.702
Have you tried it?

40:25.726 --> 40:28.205
You just want me out of my
head so I'll let you screw me again.

40:28.229 --> 40:30.774
No, you-you don't
have to do anything.

40:30.798 --> 40:34.517
I just want you to feel good.

40:35.469 --> 40:40.223
I would build you a castle, or sail
you away on a magnificent yacht.

40:41.308 --> 40:43.587
But I can't do any of that.

40:43.611 --> 40:45.822
Um, I want to make you happy.

40:45.846 --> 40:49.232
At least for a little while.

41:52.713 --> 41:56.466
I want to show you something.

42:11.398 --> 42:14.317
I don't understand.

42:14.935 --> 42:18.421
It's a shrine. To you.

42:20.274 --> 42:22.486
But why?

42:22.510 --> 42:26.963
Because I worship you, Fernande.

42:31.785 --> 42:35.699
I know you didn't
want me to draw you.

42:35.723 --> 42:38.335
Are you angry?

42:38.359 --> 42:44.614
No, I, no, it's,
you make me look so beautiful.

42:47.468 --> 42:52.455
Sometimes I can't find the
right words to say what I feel.

42:53.574 --> 42:58.428
But I can with my
pencils and brushes.

43:08.322 --> 43:10.133
You don't have to.

43:10.157 --> 43:13.509
I want to.

43:21.769 --> 43:23.780
Dora. What happened?

43:23.804 --> 43:25.749
A man attacked me.

43:25.773 --> 43:28.051
He stole my dog and my bicycle.

43:28.075 --> 43:30.120
It was terrible.

43:30.144 --> 43:33.529
We found her wandering along the river,
but there was no evidence of an attack.

43:34.248 --> 43:36.526
These idiots would not believe
me, so I made them bring me.

43:36.550 --> 43:40.036
Tell them. Tell them, Pablo.

43:40.654 --> 43:43.133
Tell them what has
happened to me.

43:43.157 --> 43:44.968
Thank you for bringing her here.

43:44.992 --> 43:46.870
You can go now.
I'll take care of her.

43:46.894 --> 43:49.739
Forgive me, Monsieur, but perhaps
you should take her to the hospital.

43:49.763 --> 43:52.348
I don't think she's
in her right mind.

43:52.366 --> 43:54.851
All right. Thank you.

43:57.371 --> 44:01.057
Oh, Pablo.

44:03.210 --> 44:04.421
Come, come, come, come, come.

44:04.445 --> 44:06.996
You crazy slut!

44:07.781 --> 44:10.117
After everything I've done
for you, you're gonna

44:10.141 --> 44:12.292
leave me for this dirty
little foreigner!

44:12.820 --> 44:16.239
If you come near
her again, I will kill you.

44:42.549 --> 44:46.202
We're going to be happy now.

44:59.500 --> 45:01.845
Is she doing any better?

45:01.869 --> 45:05.582
Uh. The doctor
gave her a sedative.

45:05.606 --> 45:07.350
Yeah, she'll be fine.

45:07.374 --> 45:08.852
She won't be fine.

45:08.876 --> 45:10.820
She's a Surrealist.

45:10.844 --> 45:14.330
They all go mad sooner or later.

45:14.581 --> 45:17.800
Pablo, that is absurd.

45:18.252 --> 45:19.596
She needs some rest.

45:19.620 --> 45:21.031
A couple of weeks in Antibes.

45:21.055 --> 45:23.700
Can't you see she's suffering?

45:23.724 --> 45:25.535
A holiday isn't
going to solve that.

45:25.559 --> 45:28.071
Oh, no?
What do you suggest then?

45:28.095 --> 45:29.873
Mademoiselle Dr. Gilot?

45:29.897 --> 45:32.248
I don't know.

45:33.100 --> 45:37.954
But what I do know is that this,

45:39.907 --> 45:44.020
what we're doing,
you think she doesn't mind,

45:44.044 --> 45:47.757
because she's such a free thinker,
but she does mind very much,

45:47.781 --> 45:50.226
and it's hurting her, and
it's making her worse.

45:50.250 --> 45:53.502
Don't be such a narcissist.

45:53.821 --> 45:56.706
It's got nothing to do with you.

45:59.059 --> 46:00.570
I'm sorry.

46:00.594 --> 46:02.572
I thought I could do things
your way, but I can't.

46:02.596 --> 46:07.149
Maybe Dora was right.
Maybe you're still a child.

46:09.603 --> 46:12.951
Maybe. But I
am going to look after

46:12.975 --> 46:15.972
myself, and I hope
you look after Dora.

46:23.984 --> 46:25.995
It will be over soon.

46:26.019 --> 46:28.571
Please. I don't
want this. Please. Please.

46:38.632 --> 46:40.816
Clear.

46:46.807 --> 46:49.986
I've told you before, no private
matters on company time.

46:50.010 --> 46:52.355
What is this nonsense?

46:52.379 --> 46:54.624
It is my work.

46:54.648 --> 46:58.200
You are confused, Kostrowistzky.
This is your work.

46:59.052 --> 47:01.097
Not anymore.

47:01.121 --> 47:04.774
I'm a published art
critic now and a poet.

47:06.627 --> 47:09.305
"Throwing his ink
towards the heavens,

47:09.329 --> 47:11.107
sucking the
blood of what he likes,

47:11.131 --> 47:15.885
and finding it delicious,
this inhuman monster.

47:16.670 --> 47:19.956
It is me!"

47:22.676 --> 47:25.828
"Brushed my shadows of the dead,

47:25.879 --> 47:28.558
The blind man
rocks pretty child,

47:28.582 --> 47:31.767
The doe with all
her fauns slips by,

47:33.520 --> 47:36.605
The dwarf observes
with saddened pose,

47:37.324 --> 47:41.577
How Harlequin magically grows."

47:44.031 --> 47:46.042
It's wonderful, Guillaume.

47:46.066 --> 47:49.546
It captures the mood
of the picture perfectly.

47:49.570 --> 47:52.421
We have done it, Pablo.

47:53.173 --> 47:56.926
All of those academic graybeards
will be apoplectic when they see it.

47:58.345 --> 48:02.131
When the Autumn Salon
opens, you'll both be sensations.

48:08.956 --> 48:11.841
They have to
accept my painting first.

48:23.270 --> 48:25.254
I'll be right back.

48:58.005 --> 49:01.323
Matisse.

49:10.350 --> 49:12.595
We're leaving.

49:12.619 --> 49:13.830
